High Level Intent
This module answers one question: What should I work on right now? It balances urgency (due date) with importance (priority) — neither factor alone is enough to rank tasks correctly.

Code with Suggested Inline Comments
def calculate_task_score(task):
    # Non-linear weights: gap between HIGH(4) and URGENT(6)
    # is intentionally wider to make urgent tasks stand out
    priority_weights = {
        TaskPriority.LOW: 1,
        TaskPriority.MEDIUM: 2,
        TaskPriority.HIGH: 4,
        TaskPriority.URGENT: 6
    }

    # Multiply by 10 to create scoring headroom for
    # additions and subtractions below
    score = priority_weights.get(task.priority, 0) * 10

    if task.due_date:
        # Negative days = task is already past deadline
        days_until_due = (task.due_date - datetime.now()).days

        # Check most urgent case first — order matters here!
        # If <= 7 was checked first, overdue tasks would only
        # get +10 instead of +35
        if days_until_due < 0:    # overdue
            score += 35
        elif days_until_due == 0: # due today
            score += 20
        elif days_until_due <= 2: # due very soon
            score += 15
        elif days_until_due <= 7: # due this week
            score += 10
        # No else — tasks due in 8+ days get +0

    # Large penalty pushes completed tasks to bottom
    # even if they were previously high priority
    if task.status == TaskStatus.DONE:
        score -= 50
    elif task.status == TaskStatus.REVIEW:
        score -= 15

    # Tags must be lowercase to match — 'Blocker' won't work
    if any(tag in ['blocker', 'critical', 'urgent'] for tag in task.tags):
        score += 8

    # Uses calendar days not hours — task updated 23hrs ago
    # on previous calendar day gets 0 bonus
    days_since_update = (datetime.now() - task.updated_at).days
    if days_since_update < 1:
        score += 5

    return score

Assumptions in the Code
•	Tags are always stored as lowercase strings
•	updated_at is always set and never None
•	Due dates are stored as datetime objects, not strings
•	Tasks always have a valid TaskPriority enum value

Potential Improvements Identified
Improvement	Reason
Add minimum score floor (e.g. 0)	Prevents confusing negative scores
Make weights configurable	Hardcoded values are hard to tune without code changes
Break ties by created_at date	Equal scores currently resolve unpredictably
Make tags case-insensitive	Use tag.lower() to prevent silent mismatches
Add score cap	No upper limit means unusual combinations score very high

